  "texts": [
    "Varying this has trivial effect on the model, though higher values can distort public knowledge.",
    "We use the Hellinger distance because it is a true distance metric that is symmetric and satisfies the triangle inequality, which is important for the innovation calculation.",
    "The Hellinger distance is bounded by 0 and 1 (if the two pdfs have no common support) and given by:H(p, q) = 1 √ 2 √ ∫ (√ p(x) -√ q(x))",
